// https://github.com/AngusJohnson/Clipper2/issues/1083
//
// A single self-intersecting polygon (~310 vertices) is fed to a Union with the
// EvenOdd fill rule in order to "simplify" it into simple (non-self-intersecting)
// polygons. Clipper2 returns 4 polygons as expected, but the 6-vertex polygon at
// index 1 is itself NOT simple (it self-intersects).
//
// The original issue uses int64 coordinates in the millions. Klip clips on raw
// floats, so we feed the same numbers directly (z values are dropped, they are
// only metadata in Clipper2 and 'Z = unit here).


